# Windows: onnxruntime-gpu 1.18+ stopped bundling CUDA/cuDNN runtime DLLs
# (~1.4 GB). The [cuda,cudnn] PyPI extras (introduced in 1.21.0) pull in
# nvidia-cublas-cu12, nvidia-cudnn-cu12, nvidia-cufft-cu12, etc. The launcher
# repair script (repair_onnxruntime.py) installs those extras only when an
# NVIDIA GPU is detected as primary, so Intel/AMD users do not pay the cost
# and get swapped to onnxruntime-directml. Older cards (RTX 40/30/20/GTX)
# still work via CUDA 12.x compatibility.
